---
// import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Container from "../../components/Container.astro";
import Image from "astro/components/Image.astro";
import gpStackedLogo from "../../assets/images/grand_place/GrandPlace_StackedLogo.svg";
---

<Layout title="Grand Place | K4D3">
  <Container>
    <header class="header-hero">
      <h1 class="case-h1">Grand Place</h1>
      <hr class="hr-color" />
    </header>

    <div class="case-study-flex">
      <div class="case-intro-text">
        <h2 class="case-subtitle">
          A new brand identity system and website for a luxury real estate team.
        </h2>
        <p>
          Grand Place Real Estate is a growing team with a mission to fulfill
          their clients' goals with seamless and trusting service. After years
          of working under Keller Williams, it became clear to the owners that
          they needed to distinguish themselves from other teams at KW. Their
          brand was unrecognizable beyond the parent brokerage. Many realtors
          face this because they rely on templates for their brand, which
          results in everyone blending in with the competition.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="case-extras">
        <div>
          <h3 class="subtag text-muted">Services</h3>

          <ul class="services">
            <li>Visual Strategy</li>
            <li>Branding</li>
            <li>Signage System</li>
            <li>Web Design</li>
            <li>WordPress Development</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="subtag web-url text-muted">Visit the site</h3>

          <div class="web-url-flex">
            <a
              class="web-url-flex"
              href="https://www.grandplacere.com/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noreferrer"
            >
              grandplacere.com
              <!-- <SquareArrowOutUpRight /> -->
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container-lg">
      <Image
        src={gpStackedLogo}
        alt="
        Grand
        Place
        stacked
        logotype"
        loading="eager"
      />
    </div>

    <div class="container pad-around grid-auto-fit">
      <h2 class="case-h2">The Solution</h2>

      <div>
        <p>
          With a new identity, they wanted their brand to target a luxury market
          while still being approachable to first-home buyers. We worked
          together to create a full branding package, with collaborative review
          at each step of the process.
        </p>
        <p class="text-highlight">
          <strong>The brand identity needed to:</strong>
        </p>
        <ul class="bullet-list">
          <li>
            Represent their professional image: modern, clean, premium,
            transparent.
          </li>
          <li>Appeal to high-end clients without feeling overly exclusive.</li>
          <li>
            Provide a polished experience that spans across all aspects of the
            business.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
      <img
        src="../assets/images/grand_place/GrandPlace_Logos_CaseStudy.webp"
        alt="Grand Place primary and secondary logos"
        width="1922"
        height="1081"
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </div>

    <div class="container pad-around grid-auto-fit">
      <h2 class="case-h2">Brand Naming</h2>
      <div>
        <p>
          Previously operating under their last name, I worked with the
          founders, George &amp; Page, to rename their company. The old name was
          difficult to remember, and they wanted a name that embraced them as
          they expanded their team.
        </p>
        <p>
          We aimed for an ownable name that evokes both luxury and
          warmth&mdash;something they'd feel proud of&mdash;eventually landing
          on Grand Place. As an added charm, the owners love that their new
          business name happens to include their initials, G + P.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
      <img
        src="../assets/images/grand_place/gp-box-and-key.webp"
        alt="Grand Place logo embossed on a box and key"
        width="1920"
        height="1080"
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </div>

    <div class="container pad-around grid-auto-fit">
      <h2 class="case-h2">Logo, Type &amp; Color</h2>
      <div>
        <p>
          I started with concept sketches, exploring many ideas and refining
          them into a few of the best options to present to the client.
        </p>
        <p>
          I knew I wanted to explore an option that emphasizes the founders'
          initials within the business name. I solved this with a custom 'GP'
          mark, integrated into the full logo. The paired logotype is a
          customized treatment of the brand's main typeface, Playfair Display.
          Poppins is used for body copy and other supporting text.
        </p>
        <p>
          Throughout the process, I enjoy considering different scenarios where
          the logo may used. This approach ensures optimization for various
          applications, having dedicated logos for each purpose.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
      <img
        class="pad-bottom-md"
        src="../assets/images/grand_place/logoprocess-gp.jpg"
        alt="Critiquing various logo options printed out on the wall"
        width="1275"
        height="858"
        loading="lazy"
      />
      <img
        class="pad-bottom-md"
        src="../assets/images/grand_place/gp-clearspace.webp"
        alt="Grand Place minimum clear space guides"
        width="1921"
        height="1081"
        loading="lazy"
      />
      <img
        class="pad-bottom-md"
        src="../assets/images/grand_place/grandplace_colorpalette.webp"
        alt="Various Grand Place logo colorways"
        width="1921"
        height="1281"
        loading="lazy"
      />
      <img
        class="pad-bottom-md"
        src="../assets/images/grand_place/BrandGuide_Presentation_Letter.webp"
        alt="Grand Place brand guidelines"
        width="2400"
        height="1854"
        loading="lazy"
      />

      <h3 class="unchosen-concepts-h3">Unchosen Concepts:</h3>
      <div class="unchosen-concepts">
        <div class="grid-auto-fit">
          <img
            src="../assets/images/grand_place/diamond-house-RD1-mockup.jpg"
            alt="Unchosen concept of a diamond inside a house shining outward"
            width="1280"
            height="1280"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <img
            src="../assets/images/grand_place/grandplace-card-mockup4.png"
            alt="Unchosen concept of a GP logomark in the shape of a key with text reading 'Grand Place' in serif and script styles."
            width="955"
            height="955"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container pad-around grid-auto-fit">
      <h2 class="case-h2">Signage &amp; Printed Material</h2>
      <p>
        With the industry's rules and regulations in mind, I applied the new
        branding to custom signs and other printed material.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="container grid-auto-fit pad-bottom-md">
      <img
        src="../assets/images/grand_place/GrandPlace_LargeSign.svg"
        alt="Grand Place large for sale sign"
        width="1920"
        height="1920.2"
        loading="lazy"
      />
      <img
        src="../assets/images/grand_place/GrandPlace_OpenHouseSign.svg"
        alt="Grand Place small open house sign"
        width="1920"
        height="1920.2"
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </div>

    <div class="container">
      <img
        class="pad-bottom-md"
        src="../assets/images/grand_place/gp-homesellersguide-mockup-v2.webp"
        alt="Grand Place Home Seller's Guide"
        width="1920"
        height="1440"
        loading="lazy"
      />
      <img
        src="../assets/images/grand_place/gp-businesscard-rd2-option2.webp"
        alt="Grand Place business cards"
        width="1920"
        height="1080"
        loading="lazy"
      />
      <img
        src="../assets/images/grand_place/GrandPlace_Logomark_Color.webp"
        alt='"GP" logomark with sunburst effect'
        width="1603"
        height="1166"
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </div>
  </Container>
</Layout>
